<Author>Brandys11
<Content>Peaceful location We stayed at his hotel 26,27th April, we found the staff very helpful and attentive. The rooms were large and the bathroom was really nice. We didn't realise that the hotel was a little way out of town, but it was a bonus, sitting outside for breakfast in the sun and watching the comings and goings on the river was very relaxing. Sadly because we spoke no German, we did have a problem getting into townand did get on the wrong train a few times, but their public transport system works like clockwork and the people were so helpful, it just added to the fun. I went with no idea of this city but found it to be clean, welcoming , very green with lots of parks and bridges, and very laid back. If you have thought of going, do so you will be glad you did. 
