<Author>Lutzi1
<Content>A good choice for the airport A pleasant stay and good value for money - we got a very good deal by shopping around on the internet. The room wasn't huge but it was comfortable enough,and the manager was extremely pleasant and helpful. When we got there they hadn't received our booking form the internet site we booked through, but he was very relaxed about it and it was all soon sorted out.He also booked us a mini bus taxi to Schoenefeld airport the next morning - for six of us, about 20 euros. Be warned, you will need to get a taxi from Koepenick station to the hotel, but it will only cost a few euros (ie less than 10)Koepenick itself was a pleasant little place to wander round, with several restaurants to choose from if you don't want to eat in the hotel. We did, and the food was delicious. The breakfast buffet was quite adequate - no comparison to the one at the Holiday Inn Schoenefeld, but then on the deal we got here, the Holiday Inn cost quite a bit more ( though their shuttle to the airport or station is free). Then again, there aren't many scenic delights to stroll round at Schoenefeld airport, so it all depends what you are looking for.As for some of the other reviews, I am baffled by people who apear internet savvy but who moan about the location of their accommodation and mark it down accordingly. Surely you would check the location on the internet before you booked it ??? Like most capital cities, Berlin is a big place, and what's handy for the airport is not going to be right next to all the sights. Is it just me ?? 
