<Author>DutchyCan
<Content>Nice hotel, definately not in the city center Stayed here for 2 nights in April. Room was okay (we have had better ones in a Courtyard). It is spacious, but the furniture does not look that attractive. The hotel is big. There are busses and trams very closeby with which we went to the U- and S-Bahn to get to the city center. That will take you about 30 minutes in total. Like that you can see parts of the city too... Since we stayed 2 more days in Berlin, but in the more centrally located Marriott hotel, we found it not that troublesome to use public transport here. The breakfast was ok. The staff was nice and friendly. Overall a good experience. 
