<Author>veggietraveller
<Content>Great hotel Stayed for 4 nights in April and loved this hotel on the River Spree.Staff could not have been more helpful and welcoming. Breakfast aboveaverage. We liked being out of the city centre although we were just getting used to the S-bahn and U-bahn system for this surburban station by the time we were leaving. We are over 60 years of age and so received a discount. We found people in the hotel and generally inBerlin so nice, friendly and helpful although our German language skills are limited. For our last day we wanted to book a package of river cruise, candlelit dinner and concert in the Orangery at the Schloss Charlottenburg and the hotel staff booked this for us. I can't recommend this hotel enough so long as you don't mind being outof the city centre. Travelling to and fro was not long but, because Koepenick is on a branch line, the timetable was slightly difficult to follow. We would definitely go back. Koepenick has nice places to eat in as well as at the hotel. 
