<Author>NehaHarish
<Content>Good Hotel, Very Poor Location We stayed at the Courtyard Mariott for 3 night in March. The hotel was great and the service was good, with friendly staff always willing to help.However, the location of the hotel was in the middle of nowhere. The main city centre was about an hour away (sometimes longer depending on the trains) from the hotel. Although there is a train station within 5-7 mins walking distance, the train runs every 20 mins and is always on time. But what we found was that it took forever to get into town and we spend nearly 3 hours a day travelling into town and back. This hotel is more suitable for business people who can afford to pay for cabs! For tourists like us, its not a good location. There are many hotels in the city centre. So do check the tube map before booking.The breakfast was poor for vegetarians. No hot breakfast apart from potatoes,the rest is all for meat eaters. So all we had was just bread and yogurt.Overall not a bad hotel, apart from hotel location and breakfast. 
