<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Great Base on a family budget Booked through internet as a base for my return trip to Berlin after approx 30 years but this time with wife and 4 children. We had 2 ajoining rooms with plenty of space, very clean, very modern, needed and recieved more pillows - it was all very efficient. Inclusive breakfast was a joy, so much to choose from and such a treat to eat outside overlooking the river, kids loved it. Hotel staff very curteous, polite, helpful and always wanting to speak English even if we tried to speak a little German! Location might put people off but once we knew the timetable for S-Bahn it was only a few minutes to walk to the station and off to the centre for sightseeing/sports/food etc. Walk across the bridge and lo and behold its like a small village town centre with some shops, trams and restaurants. I loved coming back to Berlin, I loved staying at the Courtyard and would return there as a base. Thank you easyJet and thank you Courtyard. 
